SIMPLE: metaphosphoric
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: metaphosphoric
<hw>met`a*phos*phor"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>meta-</ets> + <ets>phosphoric</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, a monobasic acid,
<chform>HPO3</chform>, analogous to nitric acid, and, by heating
phosphoric acid, obtained as a crystalline substance, commonly called
<altname>glacial phosphoric acid</altname>. Compare the tribasic
<contr>orthophosphoric acid</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metaphrase</ent>⟦br⟧
